#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an4.173"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.173:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.173:0.2"
msgid "18. Sañcetaniyavagga "
msgstr "18. Intention "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: mahākoṭṭhitasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an4.173:0.3"
msgid "173. Mahākoṭṭhikasutta "
msgstr "173. With Mahākoṭṭhita "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.161, sc1
#. VAR: mahākoṭṭhiko → mahākoṭṭhito (bj)
msgctxt "an4.173:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā mahākoṭṭhiko yenāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā sāriputtena saddhiṃ sammodi. "
msgstr "Then Venerable Mahākoṭṭhita went up to Venerable Sāriputta, and exchanged greetings with him. "

msgctxt "an4.173:1.2"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā mahākoṭṭhiko āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, Mahākoṭṭhita sat down to one side, and said to Sāriputta: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an4.173:2.1"
msgid "“Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā atthaññaṃ kiñcī”ti? "
msgstr "“Reverend, when the six fields of contact have faded away and ceased with nothing left over, does something else exist?” "

# NOTE: As per BB, comm gllesses with me havem bhani; elsewhere ma hevam and ma hevam avaca are variant readings.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an4.173:3.1"
msgid "“Mā hevaṃ, āvuso”. "
msgstr "“Don’t put it like that, reverend.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an4.173:4.1"
msgid "“Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā natthaññaṃ kiñcī”ti? "
msgstr "“Does nothing else exist?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an4.173:5.1"
msgid "“Mā hevaṃ, āvuso”. "
msgstr "“Don’t put it like that, reverend.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an4.173:6.1"
msgid "“Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā atthi ca natthi ca aññaṃ kiñcī”ti? "
msgstr "“Do both something else and nothing else exist?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an4.173:7.1"
msgid "“Mā hevaṃ, āvuso”. "
msgstr "“Don’t put it like that, reverend.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "an4.173:8.1"
msgid "“Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā nevatthi no natthaññaṃ kiñcī”ti? "
msgstr "“Do neither something else nor nothing else exist?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "an4.173:9.1"
msgid "“Mā hevaṃ, āvuso”. "
msgstr "“Don’t put it like that, reverend.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "an4.173:10.1"
msgid "“‘Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā atthaññaṃ kiñcī’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno ‘mā hevaṃ, āvuso’ti vadesi. "
msgstr "“Reverend, when asked whether—when the six fields of contact have faded away and ceased with nothing left over—something else exists, you say ‘don’t put it like that’. "

msgctxt "an4.173:10.2"
msgid "‘Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā natthaññaṃ kiñcī’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno: "
msgstr "When asked whether nothing else exists, "

msgctxt "an4.173:10.3"
msgid "‘mā hevaṃ, āvuso’ti vadesi. "
msgstr "you say ‘don’t put it like that’. "

msgctxt "an4.173:10.4"
msgid "‘Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā atthi ca natthi ca aññaṃ kiñcī’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno: "
msgstr "When asked whether both something else and nothing else exist, "

msgctxt "an4.173:10.5"
msgid "‘mā hevaṃ, āvuso’ti vadesi. "
msgstr "you say ‘don’t put it like that’. "

msgctxt "an4.173:10.6"
msgid "‘Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā nevatthi no natthaññaṃ kiñcī’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno: "
msgstr "When asked whether neither something else nor nothing else exist, "

msgctxt "an4.173:10.7"
msgid "‘mā hevaṃ, āvuso’ti vadesi. "
msgstr "you say ‘don’t put it like that’. "

msgctxt "an4.173:10.8"
msgid "Yathā kathaṃ pana, āvuso, imassa bhāsitassa attho daṭṭhabbo”ti? "
msgstr "How then should we see the meaning of this statement?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.162, sc11
msgctxt "an4.173:11.1"
msgid "“‘Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā atthaññaṃ kiñcī’ti, iti vadaṃ appapañcaṃ papañceti. "
msgstr "“If you say that, ‘When the six fields of contact have faded away and ceased with nothing left over, something else exists’, you’re proliferating the unproliferated. "

msgctxt "an4.173:11.2"
msgid "‘Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā natthaññaṃ kiñcī’ti, iti vadaṃ appapañcaṃ papañceti. "
msgstr "If you say that ‘nothing else exists’, you’re proliferating the unproliferated. "

msgctxt "an4.173:11.3"
msgid "‘Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā atthi ca natthi ca aññaṃ kiñcī’ti, iti vadaṃ appapañcaṃ papañceti. "
msgstr "If you say that ‘both something else and nothing else exist’, you’re proliferating the unproliferated. "

msgctxt "an4.173:11.4"
msgid "‘Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā nevatthi no natthaññaṃ kiñcī’ti, iti vadaṃ appapañcaṃ papañceti. "
msgstr "If you say that ‘neither something else nor nothing else exists’, you’re proliferating the unproliferated. "

msgctxt "an4.173:11.5"
msgid "Yāvatā, āvuso, channaṃ phassāyatanānaṃ gati tāvatā papañcassa gati; "
msgstr "The scope of the six fields of contact extends as far as the scope of proliferation. "

msgctxt "an4.173:11.6"
msgid "yāvatā papañcassa gati tāvatā channaṃ phassāyatanānaṃ gati. "
msgstr "The scope of proliferation extends as far as the scope of the six fields of contact. "

msgctxt "an4.173:11.7"
msgid "Channaṃ, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā papañcanirodho papañcavūpasamo”ti. "
msgstr "When the six fields of contact fade away and cease with nothing left over, proliferation stops and is stilled.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.173:11.8"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

